title: ENTSO-E Code Lists - Current version 80 - Current Release: 0 - release date= 2022-04-07
description: Complete compilation of ENTSO-E, ebIX, UN/CEFACT and Danish Code Lists used by the Danish Datahub' XML and JSON CIM based electronic documents.

StandardAddressTypeList.description: A code specifying whether (or not) the Accounting Point is part of the imbalance settlement. .

StandardAllocationModeTypeList.description: The identification of the method of allocation in an auction.

StandardAnalogTypeList.description: The identification of an analog value.

StandardAssetTypeList.description: The identification of the type of asset.

StandardAuctionTypeList.description: The coded representation of different types of auction.

StandardBusinessSectorTypeList.description: A code specifying the business sector, such as electricity or gas

StandardBusinessTypeList.description: The exact business nature identifying the principal characteristic of a time series.

StandardCategoryTypeList.description: The product category of an auction.

StandardChargeTypeList.description: A code specifying how the energy volumes are treated for settlement for an Accounting Point, such as profiled or non-profiled.

StandardClassificationTypeList.description: Indicates the classification mechanism used to group a set of objects together. The grouping may be of a detailed or a summary nature.

StandardCodingSchemeTypeList.description: Codification scheme used to identify the coding scheme used for the set of coded values to identify specific objects.

StandardContractTypeList.description:
The contract type defines the conditions under which the capacity is allocated and handled, e.g. daily auction, weekly auction, monthly auction, yearly auction, etc. 
The significance of this type is dependent on area specific coded working methods.

StandardCoordinateSystemTypeList.description: The identification of the coordinate system used for the location position.

StandardCurrencyTypeList.description: The coded identification of legal tender using ISO 4217 3 alpha codes.

StandardCurveTypeList.description: The type of curve being defined in the time series.

StandardDirectionTypeList.description: The coded identification of the direction of energy flow.

StandardDisconnectionMethodTypeList.description: A code specifying the direction of the active energy flow in this Metering Point, such as consumption, production or combined.

StandardDocumentTypeList.description:
The DocumentTypeList is only used in XML instances using deprecated ENTSO-E schema; otherwise for XML instances based CIM, the codelist is MessageTypeList. 
Therefore, you are kindly advised to refer to the MessageType enumeration, which includes the same enumeration codes.

StandardEicTypeList.description: The coded identification of the type of an EIC code.

StandardEnergyProductTypeList.description: The identification of the nature of an energy product such as power, energy, reactive power, etc.

StandardFuelTypeList.description: The identification of the type of fuel.

StandardHVDCModeTypeList.description: The coded identification of the HVDC mode.

StandardIndicatorTypeList.description: A boolean indicator to express Yes or No or True or False.

StandardMarketProductTypeList.description: The identification of the type of a product on a market view

StandardMessageTypeList.description:
The coded type of a document. The message type describes the principal characteristic of a document.
This enumeration is used in the XML instances based on IEC 62325.

StandardMeteredDataCollectionMethodTypeL.description: A code specifying how a Metered Data Collector collects data from the Meter for this Accounting Point, such as Automatic or Manually.

StandardMeteringMethodTypeList.description: A code specifying how the energy volumes are established for this Accounting Point, such as continuous- non-continuous- or not-metered.

StandardMeteringPointTypeList.description: A code specifying the direction of the active energy flow in this Metering Point, such as consumption, production or combined.

StandardMeterReadingTypeList.description: A code specifying whether (or not) the Accounting Point is part of the imbalance settlement. .

StandardMPConnectionTypeList.description: A code specifying whether (or not) the Accounting Point is part of the imbalance settlement. .

StandardObjectAggregationTypeList.description: The identification of the domain that is the common dominator used to aggregate a time series.

StandardPaymentTermsTypeList.description: The identification of the different terms of payment.

StandardPhysicalStatusTypeList.description: A code specifying the direction of the active energy flow in this Metering Point, such as consumption, production or combined.

StandardPriceCategoryTypeList.description: Indicates the category of the calculation to be applied to a price.

StandardPriceComponentTypeList.description: Indicates the component type for  a price.

StandardPriceDirectionTypeList.description: The nature of a price, i.e. an impacted area system operator pays to internal market parties or inverse.

StandardProcessTypeList.description: Indicates the nature of process that the document addresses.

StandardProcessVariantTypeList.description: A code specifying a the process variant.

StandardReasonCodeTypeList.description: The coded motivation of an act.

StandardRightsTypeList.description: The rights of use that is accorded to what is acquired in an auction.

StandardRoleTypeList.description: Identification of the role played by a party.

StandardServiceRequestTypeList.description: A code specifying a type of service the Energy Supplier can request form the Grid Company.

StandardSettlementMethodTypeList.description: A code specifying how the energy volumes are treated for settlement for an Accounting Point, such as profiled or non-profiled.

StandardStatusTypeList.description: The condition or position of an object with regard to its standing.

StandardTarifTypeTypeList.description: The standard tariff types as defined in the RGCE policies.

StandardUnitMultiplier.description: The unit multipliers defined for the CIM.

StandardUnitOfMeasureTypeList.description: (synonym MeasurementUnit) The unit of measure that is applied to a quantity. The measurement units shall be in compliance with UN/ECE Recommendation 20.

StandardUnitSymbol.description: The coded representation of different units from IEC 61970.

StandardVATPayerTypeList.description: A code specifying whether (or not) the Accounting Point is part of the imbalance settlement. .
